
# 2025-11-22 19:21:32.999894
+Code the following app
+```
+You will build a complete, interactive “Mangala” (Turkish Mancala) board game
+as a Farcaster Mini-App (Frames compatible). 
+
+IMPORTANT REQUIREMENTS:
+- Keep all UI and code FRAME-SAFE (no external heavy JS unless necessary).
+- Use simple HTML/CSS/JS or lightweight React.
+- Maintain game state between interactions.
+- Ensure the mini-app can be embedded inside a Farcaster cast.
+
+------------------------------------------
+GAME RULES — IMPLEMENT EXACTLY (MANGALA)
+------------------------------------------
+
+Board structure:
+- 2 players
+- Each player has 6 pits (P1 pits: 1–6, P2 pits: 7–12)
+- Each player has 1 store (P1 store, P2 store)
+- Each pit begins with 4 stones.
+
+Turn Rules:
+1. On your turn, choose one of your pits.
+2. Pick up all stones from that pit.
+3. Distribute stones counter-clockwise, one per pit/store.
+4. Skip opponent’s store during distribution.
+
+Capturing rule:
+- If the last stone lands in your EMPTY pit on your own side:
+  You capture that stone + all stones in the opposite pit.
+  Move them to your store.
+
+Free turn rule:
+- If the last stone lands in your own store, you get another turn.
+
+Game end rule:
+- If one side’s pits are all empty → game ends.
+- Remaining stones go to the respective player’s store.
+- Higher store count wins.
+
+------------------------------------------
+UI REQUIREMENTS
+------------------------------------------
+
+The UI must show:
+- The full Mangala board (6 pits + store per player)
+- Stones count in each pit + store
+- A clear indicator of whose turn it is
+- Buttons to select pits
+- Reset/New Game button
+- Optional: simple animations (increment/decrement, highlight last pit)
+
+The layout must work inside a Farcaster Mini-App frame:
+- Max width 420px
+- Simple and readable
+- Touch-friendly buttons
+- Minimal but pleasant styling (CSS allowed)
+
+------------------------------------------
+STATE MANAGEMENT
+------------------------------------------
+
+Your output should include:
+- Data model:
+  pits = [4,4,4,4,4,4, 4,4,4,4,4,4]
+  stores = { p1: 0, p2: 0 }
+  currentPlayer = 1 or 2
+
+- Functions:
+  makeMove(pitIndex)
+  distributeStones()
+  checkCapture()
+  checkExtraTurn()
+  checkGameOver()
+  getWinner()
+
+- UI update function:
+  renderBoard()
+
+------------------------------------------
+FARCASTER MINI-APP REQUIREMENTS
+------------------------------------------
+
+Include:
+1) Mini-App metadata:
+   <meta name="fc:frame" content="vNext">
+   <meta property="og:title" content="Mangala Mini Game">
+   <meta property="og:image" content="IMAGE_URL_HERE">
+
+2) Buttons on the frame:
+   - Buttons representing pits for the current player
+   - A "New Game" button
+   - A "Share Result" button (end screen only)
+
+3) If possible: 
+   When the game finishes, allow:
+   - Share on Farcaster → "/~/compose?text=I won Mangala! https://YOUR_APP_URL"
+   - Share on X → "https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=..."
+
+------------------------------------------
+OUTPUT FORMAT
+------------------------------------------
+
+Produce the following in the response:
+
+1) Full working mini-app code (HTML/JS or React)
+2) Explanation of all key functions
+3) List of API endpoints if needed
+4) A test simulation (example gameplay showing moves)
+
+------------------------------------------
+NOW START:
+------------------------------------------
+
+Build the FULL WORKING Mangala Mini-App code according to all rules above.
+
+```
+
+Generate an app logo and update the app metadata title and description.

